-- Nigeria to raise 138 bln naira in Treasury bills
-- 
-- Wed May 28, 2014 07:12AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, May 28 (Reuters) - Nigeria plans to issue 137.97 billion naira ($848.00 million)worth in treasury bills on June 4 with maturities ranging from three months to one year, the central bank said on Wednesday.

The bank said it would auction 22.97 billion naira worth in three-month treasury bills, 30 billion naira of six-month paper and 85 billion naira of the one-year debt note. Auction results are expected the following day, the bank said in a statement.